If a resident is adjudicated a disabled person, is found to be medically incompetent by the attending physician of the resident, or is unable to communicate with others, the rights of the resident may be exercised by:
The next of kin of the resident;
The guardian of the person of the resident;
The sponsoring agency of the resident; or
Unless the facility is the representative payee, the representative payee that the Social Security Administration designates for the resident.
